Tables needed in MariaDB (replicated from Oracle ERP):

1. scmitems
   Columns used: ITEMID, NAME, UNITOFMEASUREID, WAREHOUSEID

2. scmunitofmeasures
   Columns used: UNITOFMEASUREID, UNITOFMEASURE

3. scmitemrevisions
   Columns used: ITEMREVISIONID, ITEMID

4. scmdepartments
   Columns used: DEPARTMENTID, NAME

5. SCMQUANTITYONHAND
   Columns used: ITEMID, ONHANDQUANTITY

6. POHEADERS
   Columns used: POHEADERID, SUPPLIERID, CURRENCYID, CONVERSIONRATE

7. POLINES
   Columns used: POHEADERID, ITEMID, UNITOFMEASUREID, PRICE, STATUS, WAREHOUSEID

8. SCMUNITOFMEASURES (same as #2, joined via different alias in LPP)

9. SCMITEMS (same as #1, joined via different alias in LPP)

10. SCMCURRENCIES
    Columns used: CURRENCYID

11. SCMSUPPLIERS
    Columns used: SUPPLIERID

12. scmwarehouse
    Columns used: WAREHOUSEID, NAME (or warehouse name column)
    Note: currently we hardcode warehouse_id=1, but if you want to
    fetch the warehouse name for display, this table is needed.